text: Among the 21 % of vaccination non - responders that were older than 16 weeks , some were likely exposed to FPV prior to seroconversion , either before or after admission to the shelter , as indicated by the median vaccination - to - diagnosis interval of 7 . 5 days . The incubation period for FPL is between 2 and 10 days [ 17 ] . Other reasons for apparent vaccine failure include persistence of MDA for > 16 weeks in kittens born to queens with high anti - FPV antibody titres or failure to mount an immune response to v because of immunodeficiency ( acquired or genetic ) , incorrect vaccine administration or storage errors [ 35 , 38 ] .
